comments: Barrett (NYK) is moving alongside Gordon's (ORL) path and absorbs the body contact made with Gordon at the end of the drive.

Randle (NYK) and Barrett (NYK) each make incidental contact with Birch (ORL) as all three attempt to gain control of the loose ball. Barrett and Birch tie each other up and a jump ball is correctly assessed.
Bullock (NYK) brushes Ross' (ORL) backside as he gains control of the ball and marginal contact occurs.
Birch (ORL) initiates contact with Randle's (NYK) upper half that affects his FOM off ball.
Payton (NYK) places his hand to Anthony's (ORL) front and left side before correcting.
Robinson (NYK) and Vucevic (ORL) engage and disengage with one another as they move through the lane toward the block.
Bullock (NYK) has his hand on Ross' (ORL) left side before correcting.
Gordon (ORL) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.

Randle (NYK) has his right arm extended when some contact occurs with Birch's (ORL) head as Randle receives the pass. Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Randle (NYK) goes to, not through, Birch's (ORL) space and spins off of the contact made in the lane.
Vucevic (ORL) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it from Barrett (NYK) prior to incidental contact taking place.
Birch (ORL) is moving alongside Barrett's (NYK) path, and marginal body contact takes place during Barrett's drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Robinson (NYK) maintains legal guarding position as contact occurs with Gordon (ORL) during the driving shot attempt.

As Gordon (ORL) continues to jump backward following the put-back attempt, Randle's (NYK) arm comes forward and some contact occurs with Gordon's face/upper half. Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Randle (NYK) and Birch (ORL) make incidental contact with one another as they each attempt to gain control of the loose ball.
Anthony (ORL) and Randle (NYK) make incidental contact with one another as they each attempt to retrieve the loose ball. A jump ball is correctly assessed.
Birch (ORL) commits the take foul on Bullock (NYK).
Bullock (NYK) rests his right hand on Anthony's (ORL) shoulder after the shot is released and removes it as marginal contact occurs.
Vucevic (ORL) commits the take foul on Randle (NYK).
Randle (NYK) maintains legal guarding position as contact occurs with Gordon (ORL) at the end of the drive.
Bacon (ORL) commits the take foul on Randle (NYK).
